******
[3] Sichuan
Date: Thu 9 Mar 2017 7:46 PM CST
Source: FIC (Flu Information Centre/Flu in China) [edited]
http://www.flu.org.cn/en/news-19142.html


After the confirmation by Sichuan provincial CDC lab, Sichuan reported 3 human H7N9 AIV cases. Wusheng county of Guang'an city confirmed one human H7N9 AIV case on [7 Mar 2017]. The 65 year old female patient lived in Huafeng town of Wusheng county.

Shunqing district of Nanchong city [Sichuan province] confirmed one human H7N9 AIV case on [7 Mar 2017]. The 45 year old male patient lived in Shunqing district of Nanchong city, worked in a live poultry slaughter site in Dabei road market. He was admitted as an emergency at the city central hospital on 8 pm [5 Mar 2017]. Both cases are in a critical condition and in hospital for treatment.

Kaijiang county of Dazhou city [Sichuan province] confirmed one human H7N9 AIV case on [8 Mar 2017]. The 64 year old male patient lived in Xintai town of Kaijiang county. He died after treatment in Dazhou city central hospital.

All close contacts of the cases above are under medical monitoring.

By 5 pm, [9 Mar 2017], Sichuan has reported 11 cases of human H7N9 AIV infection. They are 5 cases in Suining city (3 fatal, one cured), one case in Deyang city, 3 cases in Guang an city (2 fatal), one case in Nanchong city, and one case in Dazhou city (fatal).

--
communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[This report covers 5 recent cases reported since the last update on 7 Mar 2017. All reports indicate that epidemiological investigations were undertaken and some cases had exposure to wet market poultry, followed by illness. All identified contacts are being monitored for symptoms of influenza like illness. However, continued occurrence of these cases mandates that stricter preventive measures be implemented in the wet markets to reduce transmission. - Mod.UBA

Maps of China can be seen at http://www.sacu.org/maps/provmap.png and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4890695,155. - Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ]
